Program: Great Lives
Title: Tom Shakespeare on Gramsci
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04fz6ky
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 5 Sep 2014
Dr Tom Shakespeare, lecturer at the Medical School in the University of East Anglia and prominent campaigner for the rights of the disabled, explains to Matthew Parris why the life and work of the Italian left-wing revolutionary Antonio Gramsci means a great deal to him personally. They are joined in the studio by Professor Anne Sassoon. Producer Christine Hall. Show less